result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeffery A Hynous was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[ml] Case called at 3:05PM
Defendant Jeffery A Hynous in court with attorney Patrick Kiernan Cafferty. DA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.

Maximum penalties are recited; Constitutional rights are reviewed; plea of " GUILTY " entered as to Count #1 and #2; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance is verified.  The Court accepts the plea, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count #3.

As to Count #1, the Court sentences the Defendant to:
--serve 30 days in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges, concurrent to Count #2 but consecutive to any other sentence; the Court allows transfer of this sentence to Walworth County under the conditions that Walworth County accept the transfer and that there be no electronic monitoring; to commence on 07/23 at 12:00 noon

As to Count #2, the Court sentences the Defendant to:
--serve 30 days in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges, concurrent to Count #1, but consecutive to any other sentence; the Court allows transfer of this sentence to Walworth County under the conditions that Walworth County accept the transfer and that there be no electronic monitoring to commence on 07/23 at 12:00 noon.

As to both files:
--Mr. Hynous is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without non-prescribed controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber privileges without further process.
--pay costs plus DNA surcharge= $886.00, The Court grants the Defendant sixty days to pay the amount in full or to establish a payment plan with the Clerk of Courts Office. Non-payment will result in a 20 day jail term with Huber privileges, consecutive to any other sentence.
The Court orders the Defendant to comply with DNA sample provision today.

Days credit for time already served: 1 day
